@node Segment visibility
@section Segment visibility

@vindex doom-modeline-extras-org-roam
@vindex doom-modeline-extras-tlon-split
@vindex doom-modeline-extras-ai-context
@vindex doom-modeline-extras-claude-code
The user option @code{doom-modeline-extras-org-roam} controls whether the Org
Roam backlink count segment is displayed.  When non-@code{nil} (the default),
the backlink count appears in the modeline while visiting an Org mode
buffer that has backlinks.  Set it to @code{nil} to hide this segment.

The user option @code{doom-modeline-extras-tlon-split} controls whether the
Tlon split mode indicator is shown.  The default value is @code{t}.  When
@code{tlon-split-mode} is active and this option is non-@code{nil}, the word
``split'' appears in the modeline.

The user option @code{doom-modeline-extras-ai-context} controls whether the
AI context file count is displayed.  The default value is @code{t}.  When
non-@code{nil} and there are files in the @code{gptel-context--alist}, the count
appears as a sparkle icon with a number.

The user option @code{doom-modeline-extras-claude-code} controls whether the
Claude Code status segment is displayed in Claude Code buffers.  The
default value is @code{t}.

@node Claude Code cost display
@section Claude Code cost display

@vindex doom-modeline-extras-claude-code-api-plan
The user option @code{doom-modeline-extras-claude-code-api-plan} determines
how session costs are rendered in the Claude Code modeline segment.
When @code{nil} (the default), the package assumes a subscription plan (Free,
Pro, or Max) and displays the cost with a strikethrough face to indicate
that the amount is not actually charged.  When non-@code{nil}, it assumes an
API plan and displays the cost normally, since the user is paying per
token.

The boolean type accepts @code{t} or @code{nil}.  You should set this to @code{t} if
you are using the Claude API directly rather than a subscription plan.

